Text.Value: You! You an adventurer? Looking to pad your purse? Find their foxhole, bring me their chief's head. The Fist will reward you well.
Bloody gnomes. Think they can get away with anything.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Player went through checkpoint, no gnomes. Guard still gives quest to kill gnomes

Text.Value: Damn - he's got the eyes of a rodent, and the smell to match. You did the Gate proud.
You'll change your mind once they kill innocent citizens. The only language they'll understand is that of intimidating violence.
You want through? Talk to Edwynna.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If player hasn't yet gotten approval through checkpoint, this guard won't give the quest.

Text.Value: Damn right it's a problem! I won't harm a single hair on their heads.
I won't do it.
Afraid your payday's been canceled. Budget cuts and all that.
Almost forgot - here's your coins. Now keep your nose clean and your tongue still.
Bloody gnomes.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The guard gives a "quest" to find the gnomes. But in fact it's just a way to involve player into gnomes' story. At the end of the day, the guard will say that they're too busy to bother about any refugees.

Text.Value: I agree. But we can't leave our posts, not with all the patriars meeting in Wyrm's Rock for the coronation.
But something tells me you're not hurting for coin. A good, discreet killer's always in demand.
You've the right look. Shifty eyes. A bit pale. The kind that cleans up vermin for pay.
A job for the Blade, I'd say. Clean up the rabble, keep the Gate safe.
You've the right look. Solid bones. Steady face. The kind that cleans up vermin for pay.
No time for chatter.
I see nothing but an empty hand. Enough games - bring me the gnome's head.
Then get back to it. It's only a matter of time before they do some real harm.
Out of the way.
You got the gnome leader's head?
This sounds like a job for the Flaming Fist.
Provide Wulbren's head.
Almost forgot - here's your generous fee. Now keep your nose clean and your tongue still.
We need to find where they burrowed themselves up.
You don't got a problem with that, do you? Those blasted thugs are a stain on your kind.
Bring you their head? That sounds radical.
I'll take the job. I'll find their hideout and bring the leader's head.
Leave.
Not yet, I'm afraid.
I've changed my mind. I won't kill the gnomes.
Leave.
No matter - I'll find someone else. Most folks around here'll do almost anything, you pay them enough.
I agree. But we can't leave our posts, not with all the refugees swarming Wyrm's Crossing.
Bring the head back here when it's done. I'll be around.
Then you're no friend of the Fist.
Would hate to see you meet the same fate.
Kneelickers threw explosives at the Steel Watch.
Good. Sniff them out, gut them clean. Keep Baldur's Gate safe.

Synopsis: Flaming Fist guard at WYR South checkpoint that gives a quest to kill Ironhand gnomes
